# CrunchyCone Platform Rules

## When This Applies

Only when:
- `crunchycone.toml` exists in project root, OR
- User mentions CrunchyCone deployment/integration

**Without `crunchycone.toml`:** Skip these steps entirely.

## Quick Setup

```bash
# Initialize (creates crunchycone.toml)
npx --yes crunchycone-cli project init

# Authenticate
npx --yes crunchycone-cli auth login

# Link project
npx --yes crunchycone-cli project link --setup
```

## Status Check

```bash
# Verify setup
npx --yes crunchycone-cli auth check && ls crunchycone.toml
```

## Common Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `crunchycone-cli auth check` | Check auth status |
| `crunchycone-cli auth login` | Authenticate |
| `crunchycone-cli project init` | Create config file |
| `crunchycone-cli project link --setup` | Link to platform |
| `crunchycone-cli project builds` | List recent builds |
| `crunchycone-cli project builds log <id>` | View build logs |
| `crunchycone-cli env list` | List env vars |
| `crunchycone-cli secrets set KEY value` | Set secret |

## Build Monitoring

```bash
# Check recent builds
npx --yes crunchycone-cli project builds

# View failed build logs
npx --yes crunchycone-cli project builds log <buildId>
```

## Common Build Failures

- Missing environment variables
- TypeScript compilation errors
- Database migration issues
- Missing `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"`

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| "Command not found" | `npm install` |
| "Not authenticated" | `crunchycone-cli auth login` |
| Missing config | `crunchycone-cli project init` |

## Notes

- `crunchycone.toml` should be committed to Git
- Credentials stored locally in home directory
- Auth persists across terminal sessions
